Let us now look at some examples of activation functions.
The heaviside function is defined as:
\[\begin{align*}
\rho(x) &=
\begin{cases}
1, & x &gt; 0 \\
0, & x \leq 0
\end{cases}
\end{align*}\]
The sigmoid function is defined as:
\[\begin{align*}
\rho(x) &= \frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}
\end{align*}\]


